description = "A smart city is able to report the quality of the air in each of its neighborhoods. Both cities and neighborhoods have unique names. In each neighborhood, there are several sensors to measure different pollutants which are CO, O3, SO2, NO2 and others. The measurements of those sensors are aggregated and the Air Quality Index (AQI) is calculated. This value goes from 0 to 500 degrees. This resulting index is displayed in a display located in the center of the neighborhood. For each display, its size and resolution are known"